38static bool intel_dp_mst_compute_config(struct intel_encoder *encoder,
39 struct intel_crtc_state *pipe_config)
40{
41 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->base.dev;
42 struct intel_dp_mst_encoder *intel_mst = enc_to_mst(&encoder->base);
43 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = intel_mst->primary;
44 struct intel_dp *intel_dp = &intel_dig_port->dp;
45 struct drm_atomic_state *state;
46 int bpp, i;
47 int lane_count, slots;
48 const struct drm_display_mode *adjusted_mode = &pipe_config->base.adjusted_mode;
49 struct drm_connector *drm_connector;
50 struct intel_connector *connector, *found = NULL;
51 struct drm_connector_state *connector_state;
52 int mst_pbn;
53
54 pipe_config->dp_encoder_is_mst = true;
55 pipe_config->has_pch_encoder = false;
56 pipe_config->has_dp_encoder = true;
57 bpp = 24;
58 /*
59 * for MST we always configure max link bw - the spec doesn't
60 * seem to suggest we should do otherwise.
61 */
62 lane_count = drm_dp_max_lane_count(intel_dp->dpcd);
63
64
65 pipe_config->lane_count = lane_count;
66
67 pipe_config->pipe_bpp = 24;
68 pipe_config->port_clock = intel_dp_max_link_rate(intel_dp);
69
70 state = pipe_config->base.state;
71
72 for_each_connector_in_state(state, drm_connector, connector_state, i) {
73 connector = to_intel_connector(drm_connector);
74
75 if (connector_state->best_encoder == &encoder->base) {
76 found = connector;
77 break;
78 }
79 }
80
81 if (!found) {
82 DRM_ERROR("can't find connector\n");
83 return false;
84 }
85
86 mst_pbn = drm_dp_calc_pbn_mode(adjusted_mode->crtc_clock, bpp);
87
88 pipe_config->pbn = mst_pbn;
89 slots = drm_dp_find_vcpi_slots(&intel_dp->mst_mgr, mst_pbn);
90
91 intel_link_compute_m_n(bpp, lane_count,
92 adjusted_mode->crtc_clock,
93 pipe_config->port_clock,
94 &pipe_config->dp_m_n);
95
96 pipe_config->dp_m_n.tu = slots;
97
98 if (IS_HASWELL(dev) || IS_BROADWELL(dev))
99 hsw_dp_set_ddi_pll_sel(pipe_config);
100
101 return true;
102
103}
104
105static void intel_mst_disable_dp(struct intel_encoder *encoder)
106{
107 struct intel_dp_mst_encoder *intel_mst = enc_to_mst(&encoder->base);
108 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = intel_mst->primary;
109 struct intel_dp *intel_dp = &intel_dig_port->dp;
110 int ret;
111
112 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("%d\n", intel_dp->active_mst_links);
113
114 drm_dp_mst_reset_vcpi_slots(&intel_dp->mst_mgr, intel_mst->port);
115
116 ret = drm_dp_update_payload_part1(&intel_dp->mst_mgr);
117 if (ret) {
118 DRM_ERROR("failed to update payload %d\n", ret);
119 }
120}
121
122static void intel_mst_post_disable_dp(struct intel_encoder *encoder)
123{
124 struct intel_dp_mst_encoder *intel_mst = enc_to_mst(&encoder->base);
125 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = intel_mst->primary;
126 struct intel_dp *intel_dp = &intel_dig_port->dp;
127
128 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("%d\n", intel_dp->active_mst_links);
129
130 /* this can fail */
131 drm_dp_check_act_status(&intel_dp->mst_mgr);
132 /* and this can also fail */
133 drm_dp_update_payload_part2(&intel_dp->mst_mgr);
134
135 drm_dp_mst_deallocate_vcpi(&intel_dp->mst_mgr, intel_mst->port);
136
137 intel_dp->active_mst_links--;
138 intel_mst->port = NULL;
139 if (intel_dp->active_mst_links == 0) {
140 intel_dig_port->base.post_disable(&intel_dig_port->base);
141 intel_dp_sink_dpms(intel_dp, DRM_MODE_DPMS_OFF);
142 }
143}

145static void intel_mst_pre_enable_dp(struct intel_encoder *encoder)
146{
147 struct intel_dp_mst_encoder *intel_mst = enc_to_mst(&encoder->base);
148 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = intel_mst->primary;
149 struct intel_dp *intel_dp = &intel_dig_port->dp;
150 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->base.dev;
151 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
152 enum port port = intel_dig_port->port;
153 int ret;
154 uint32_t temp;
155 struct intel_connector *found = NULL, *connector;
156 int slots;
157 struct drm_crtc *crtc = encoder->base.crtc;
158 struct intel_crtc *intel_crtc = to_intel_crtc(crtc);
159
160 for_each_intel_connector(dev, connector) {
161 if (connector->base.state->best_encoder == &encoder->base) {
162 found = connector;
163 break;
164 }
165 }
166
167 if (!found) {
168 DRM_ERROR("can't find connector\n");
169 return;
170 }
171
172 /* MST encoders are bound to a crtc, not to a connector,
173 * force the mapping here for get_hw_state.
174 */
175 found->encoder = encoder;
176
177 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("%d\n", intel_dp->active_mst_links);
178 intel_mst->port = found->port;
179
180 if (intel_dp->active_mst_links == 0) {
181 enum port port = intel_ddi_get_encoder_port(encoder);
182
183 intel_dp_set_link_params(intel_dp, intel_crtc->config);
184
185 /* FIXME: add support for SKL */
186 if (INTEL_INFO(dev)->gen < 9)
187 I915_WRITE(PORT_CLK_SEL(port),
188 intel_crtc->config->ddi_pll_sel);
189
190 intel_ddi_init_dp_buf_reg(&intel_dig_port->base);
191
192 intel_dp_sink_dpms(intel_dp, DRM_MODE_DPMS_ON);
193
194
195 intel_dp_start_link_train(intel_dp);
196 intel_dp_stop_link_train(intel_dp);
197 }
198
199 ret = drm_dp_mst_allocate_vcpi(&intel_dp->mst_mgr,
200 intel_mst->port,
201 intel_crtc->config->pbn, &slots);
202 if (ret == false) {
203 DRM_ERROR("failed to allocate vcpi\n");
204 return;
205 }
206
207
208 intel_dp->active_mst_links++;
209 temp = I915_READ(DP_TP_STATUS(port));
210 I915_WRITE(DP_TP_STATUS(port), temp);
211
212 ret = drm_dp_update_payload_part1(&intel_dp->mst_mgr);
213}
214
215static void intel_mst_enable_dp(struct intel_encoder *encoder)
216{
217 struct intel_dp_mst_encoder *intel_mst = enc_to_mst(&encoder->base);
218 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = intel_mst->primary;
219 struct intel_dp *intel_dp = &intel_dig_port->dp;
220 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dig_port->base.base.dev;
221 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
222 enum port port = intel_dig_port->port;
223 int ret __unused;
224
225 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("%d\n", intel_dp->active_mst_links);
226
227 if (wait_for((I915_READ(DP_TP_STATUS(port)) & DP_TP_STATUS_ACT_SENT),
228 1))
229 DRM_ERROR("Timed out waiting for ACT sent\n");
230
231 ret = drm_dp_check_act_status(&intel_dp->mst_mgr);
232
233 ret = drm_dp_update_payload_part2(&intel_dp->mst_mgr);
234}

237 enum i915_pipe *pipe)
238{
239 struct intel_dp_mst_encoder *intel_mst = enc_to_mst(&encoder->base);
240 *pipe = intel_mst->pipe;
241 if (intel_mst->port)
242 return true;
243 return false;
244}

246static void intel_dp_mst_enc_get_config(struct intel_encoder *encoder,
247 struct intel_crtc_state *pipe_config)
248{
249 struct intel_dp_mst_encoder *intel_mst = enc_to_mst(&encoder->base);
250 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = intel_mst->primary;
251 struct intel_crtc *crtc = to_intel_crtc(encoder->base.crtc);
252 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->base.dev;
253 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
254 enum transcoder cpu_transcoder = pipe_config->cpu_transcoder;
255 u32 temp, flags = 0;
256
257 pipe_config->has_dp_encoder = true;
258
259 temp = I915_READ(TRANS_DDI_FUNC_CTL(cpu_transcoder));
260 if (temp & TRANS_DDI_PHSYNC)
261 flags |= DRM_MODE_FLAG_PHSYNC;
262 else
263 flags |= DRM_MODE_FLAG_NHSYNC;
264 if (temp & TRANS_DDI_PVSYNC)
265 flags |= DRM_MODE_FLAG_PVSYNC;
266 else
267 flags |= DRM_MODE_FLAG_NVSYNC;
268
269 switch (temp & TRANS_DDI_BPC_MASK) {
270 case TRANS_DDI_BPC_6:
271 pipe_config->pipe_bpp = 18;
272 break;
273 case TRANS_DDI_BPC_8:
274 pipe_config->pipe_bpp = 24;
275 break;
276 case TRANS_DDI_BPC_10:
277 pipe_config->pipe_bpp = 30;
278 break;
279 case TRANS_DDI_BPC_12:
280 pipe_config->pipe_bpp = 36;
281 break;
282 default:
283 break;
284 }
285 pipe_config->base.adjusted_mode.flags |= flags;
286
287 pipe_config->lane_count =
288 ((temp & DDI_PORT_WIDTH_MASK) >> DDI_PORT_WIDTH_SHIFT) + 1;
289
290 intel_dp_get_m_n(crtc, pipe_config);
291
292 intel_ddi_clock_get(&intel_dig_port->base, pipe_config);
293}

295static int intel_dp_mst_get_ddc_modes(struct drm_connector *connector)
296{
297 struct intel_connector *intel_connector = to_intel_connector(connector);
298 struct intel_dp *intel_dp = intel_connector->mst_port;
299 struct edid *edid;
300 int ret;
301
302 edid = drm_dp_mst_get_edid(connector, &intel_dp->mst_mgr, intel_connector->port);
303 if (!edid)
304 return 0;
305
306 ret = intel_connector_update_modes(connector, edid);
307 kfree(edid);
308
309 return ret;
310}

329static void
330intel_dp_mst_connector_destroy(struct drm_connector *connector)
331{

335 kfree(intel_connector->edid);
336
337 drm_connector_cleanup(connector);
338 kfree(connector);
339}

357static enum drm_mode_status
358intel_dp_mst_mode_valid(struct drm_connector *connector,
359 struct drm_display_mode *mode)
360{
361 /* TODO - validate mode against available PBN for link */
362 if (mode->clock < 10000)
363 return MODE_CLOCK_LOW;
364
365 if (mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_DBLCLK)
366 return MODE_H_ILLEGAL;
367
368 return MODE_OK;
369}

371static struct drm_encoder *intel_mst_atomic_best_encoder(struct drm_connector *connector,
372 struct drm_connector_state *state)
373{
374 struct intel_connector *intel_connector = to_intel_connector(connector);
375 struct intel_dp *intel_dp = intel_connector->mst_port;
376 struct intel_crtc *crtc = to_intel_crtc(state->crtc);
377
378 return &intel_dp->mst_encoders[crtc->pipe]->base.base;
379}

381static struct drm_encoder *intel_mst_best_encoder(struct drm_connector *connector)
382{
383 struct intel_connector *intel_connector = to_intel_connector(connector);
384 struct intel_dp *intel_dp = intel_connector->mst_port;
385 return &intel_dp->mst_encoders[0]->base.base;
386}

407static bool intel_dp_mst_get_hw_state(struct intel_connector *connector)
408{
409 if (connector->encoder && connector->base.state->crtc) {
410 enum i915_pipe pipe;
411 if (!connector->encoder->get_hw_state(connector->encoder, &pipe))
412 return false;
413 return true;
414 }
415 return false;
416}

434static struct drm_connector *intel_dp_add_mst_connector(struct drm_dp_mst_topology_mgr *mgr, struct drm_dp_mst_port *port, const char *pathprop)
435{
436 struct intel_dp *intel_dp = container_of(mgr, struct intel_dp, mst_mgr);
437 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
438 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dig_port->base.base.dev;
439 struct intel_connector *intel_connector;
440 struct drm_connector *connector;
441 int i;
442
443 intel_connector = intel_connector_alloc();
444 if (!intel_connector)
445 return NULL;
446
447 connector = &intel_connector->base;
448 drm_connector_init(dev, connector, &intel_dp_mst_connector_funcs, DRM_MODE_CONNECTOR_DisplayPort);
449 drm_connector_helper_add(connector, &intel_dp_mst_connector_helper_funcs);
450
451 intel_connector->unregister = intel_connector_unregister;
452 intel_connector->get_hw_state = intel_dp_mst_get_hw_state;
453 intel_connector->mst_port = intel_dp;
454 intel_connector->port = port;
455
456 for (i = PIPE_A; i <= PIPE_C; i++) {
457 drm_mode_connector_attach_encoder(&intel_connector->base,
458 &intel_dp->mst_encoders[i]->base.base);
459 }
460 intel_dp_add_properties(intel_dp, connector);
461
462 drm_object_attach_property(&connector->base, dev->mode_config.path_property, 0);
463 drm_object_attach_property(&connector->base, dev->mode_config.tile_property, 0);
464
465 drm_mode_connector_set_path_property(connector, pathprop);
466 return connector;
467}
468
469static void intel_dp_register_mst_connector(struct drm_connector *connector)
470{
471 struct intel_connector *intel_connector = to_intel_connector(connector);
472 struct drm_device *dev = connector->dev;
473 drm_modeset_lock_all(dev);
474 intel_connector_add_to_fbdev(intel_connector);
475 drm_modeset_unlock_all(dev);
476 drm_connector_register(&intel_connector->base);
477}
478
479static void intel_dp_destroy_mst_connector(struct drm_dp_mst_topology_mgr *mgr,
480 struct drm_connector *connector)
481{
482 struct intel_connector *intel_connector = to_intel_connector(connector);
483 struct drm_device *dev = connector->dev;
484
485 intel_connector->unregister(intel_connector);
486
487 /* need to nuke the connector */
488 drm_modeset_lock_all(dev);
489 if (connector->state->crtc) {
490 struct drm_mode_set set;
491 int ret;
492
493 memset(&set, 0, sizeof(set));
494 set.crtc = connector->state->crtc,
495
496 ret = drm_atomic_helper_set_config(&set);
497
498 WARN(ret, "Disabling mst crtc failed with %i\n", ret);
499 }
500
501 intel_connector_remove_from_fbdev(intel_connector);
502 drm_connector_cleanup(connector);
503 drm_modeset_unlock_all(dev);
504
505 kfree(intel_connector);
506 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("\n");
507}

509static void intel_dp_mst_hotplug(struct drm_dp_mst_topology_mgr *mgr)
510{
511 struct intel_dp *intel_dp = container_of(mgr, struct intel_dp, mst_mgr);
512 struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port = dp_to_dig_port(intel_dp);
513 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dig_port->base.base.dev;
514
515 drm_kms_helper_hotplug_event(dev);
516}

518static struct drm_dp_mst_topology_cbs mst_cbs = {
519 .add_connector = intel_dp_add_mst_connector,
520 .register_connector = intel_dp_register_mst_connector,
521 .destroy_connector = intel_dp_destroy_mst_connector,
522 .hotplug = intel_dp_mst_hotplug,
523};

525static struct intel_dp_mst_encoder *
526intel_dp_create_fake_mst_encoder(struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port, enum i915_pipe pipe)
527{
528 struct intel_dp_mst_encoder *intel_mst;
529 struct intel_encoder *intel_encoder;
530 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dig_port->base.base.dev;
531
532 intel_mst = kzalloc(sizeof(*intel_mst), GFP_KERNEL);
533
534 if (!intel_mst)
535 return NULL;
536
537 intel_mst->pipe = pipe;
538 intel_encoder = &intel_mst->base;
539 intel_mst->primary = intel_dig_port;
540
541 drm_encoder_init(dev, &intel_encoder->base, &intel_dp_mst_enc_funcs,
542 DRM_MODE_ENCODER_DPMST);
543
544 intel_encoder->type = INTEL_OUTPUT_DP_MST;
545 intel_encoder->crtc_mask = 0x7;
546 intel_encoder->cloneable = 0;
547
548 intel_encoder->compute_config = intel_dp_mst_compute_config;
549 intel_encoder->disable = intel_mst_disable_dp;
550 intel_encoder->post_disable = intel_mst_post_disable_dp;
551 intel_encoder->pre_enable = intel_mst_pre_enable_dp;
552 intel_encoder->enable = intel_mst_enable_dp;
553 intel_encoder->get_hw_state = intel_dp_mst_enc_get_hw_state;
554 intel_encoder->get_config = intel_dp_mst_enc_get_config;
555
556 return intel_mst;
557
558}

560static bool
561intel_dp_create_fake_mst_encoders(struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port)
562{
563 int i;
564 struct intel_dp *intel_dp = &intel_dig_port->dp;
565
566 for (i = PIPE_A; i <= PIPE_C; i++)
567 intel_dp->mst_encoders[i] = intel_dp_create_fake_mst_encoder(intel_dig_port, i);
568 return true;
569}
570
571int
572intel_dp_mst_encoder_init(struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port, int conn_base_id)
573{
574 struct intel_dp *intel_dp = &intel_dig_port->dp;
575 struct drm_device *dev = intel_dig_port->base.base.dev;
576 int ret;
577
578 intel_dp->can_mst = true;
579 intel_dp->mst_mgr.cbs = &mst_cbs;
580
581 /* create encoders */
582 intel_dp_create_fake_mst_encoders(intel_dig_port);
583 ret = drm_dp_mst_topology_mgr_init(&intel_dp->mst_mgr, dev->dev, &intel_dp->aux, 16, 3, conn_base_id);
584 if (ret) {
585 intel_dp->can_mst = false;
586 return ret;
587 }
588 return 0;
589}
590
591void
592intel_dp_mst_encoder_cleanup(struct intel_digital_port *intel_dig_port)
593{
594 struct intel_dp *intel_dp = &intel_dig_port->dp;
595
596 if (!intel_dp->can_mst)
597 return;
598
599 drm_dp_mst_topology_mgr_destroy(&intel_dp->mst_mgr);
600 /* encoders will get killed by normal cleanup */
601}
